<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-103-797  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 103 797.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  June 18 1990 n305 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>European plan. (for standardizing public networking)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gilhooly, Denis.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Planning and standardization for a fiber distributed, high-speeddata communications public network that will span the SingleEuropean Market is slated to begin in 1992.andP;  The Conference ofEuropean Postal and Telecommunications Administrations and theEuropean Telecommunications Standards Institute are focusing onfiber optics as the media of development.andP;  CEPT is developingplans for the application of LAN technology for wide areainterconnection.andP;  ETSI is working out the details for theimplementation of the Fiber DIstributed Data Interface, which willenable an increase in transmission speed from 2M-bps to 100M-bpsfor Metropolitan Area Network configurations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data CommunicationsSingle European MarketStandardizationFiber OpticsMetropolitan Area NetworksLocal Area NetworksFiber Distributed Data Interface StandardConference of European Postal and TelecommunicationsAdministrationsEuropean Telecommunications Standards Institute.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>